Look, you wanted an article. Here is an article. Don't act surprised that it's about a Hungarian-British physicist who lived from 1900 to 1979. You asked.

A note on naming conventions, because humans are so particular about them: the native form of this [personal name](/Personal_name) is Gábor Dénes, or more accurately, Günszberg Dénes. This piece, however, will adhere to the [Western name order](/Personal_name) when discussing individuals. Try to keep up.

### Dennis Gabor

[CBE](/Order_of_the_British_Empire) [FRS](/Fellow_of_the_Royal_Society)

Gabor, captured in 1971, likely contemplating the sheer effort of it all.

